# Git Commits

Remote: `https://github.com/aryelpanda/game-project.git`

## Required Behavior

- **NEVER commit without explicit user permission.**
- After completing any code or doc change, **ask the user** whether they want a commit.
- Do not stage or commit proactively, even if changes look ready.
- Only commit when the user says yes (e.g. "commit", "yes, commit", "go ahead and commit").

## When the User Approves a Commit

1. Run `git status` and `git diff` to review changes.
2. Stage only relevant files (never secrets or debug artifacts).
3. Write a concise commit message focused on **why**, not just what.
4. Commit, then run `git status` to verify success.
5. Do **not** push unless the user explicitly asks.

## Forbidden

- Committing without permission.
- Pushing without permission.
- Amending or force-pushing without explicit request.
